==English==

===Etymology 1===
Latin: ''fons'': fountain.

====Alternative spellings====
*[[fount]]

====Noun====
'''font'''  (''plural:'' '''[[fonts]]''')
# A [[fountain]].
# A receptacle in a church for holy water - especially one used in [[baptism]]
# A receptacle for oil in a lamp.

===Etymology 2===
Old French ''[[fondre]]'': to melt.

====Noun====
'''font'''  (''plural:'' '''[[fonts]]''')
# A grouping of consistently designed [[glyph]]s, usually intended for use in [[typeset]]ting.

